<p>President Trump announced a presidential determination to set the US refugee admissions ceiling at 7,500 for fiscal year 2026, a sharp reduction from recent levels and the lowest such cap in modern practice . The Federal Register notice says the limit is “justified by humanitarian concerns or is otherwise in the national interest” and indicates admissions will be allocated primarily to white South Africans and “other victims of illegal or unjust discrimination” . Rights organisations and Democratic lawmakers immediately criticised the move as legally biased and morally troubling .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/cX47eNRPNgQ-v3Mn54i_0Ac_EUnUekH_SNThNWVRjz8VUDENM3hQBdgqq76pV1aimanHf-eJ9w_-LmjT3pmraH7PE5CI3RPRO-1o8qHvaGbxXKxfCYc2Q_vKkfTKl7oAqw5GGM2laEOzMHM_Qcq8dnGvDMLdzZCn_XvdMlFpv6MGv__kOo3a2aRxNDxK2zhvAVrMFHhIl2NPJ-qEuQ' alt='White South Africans pictured in May 2025 (image used by reporting outlets)' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Legal wording: The Federal Register text uses the term “primarily” when describing allocation to white South Africans and also references ‘other victims of illegal or unjust discrimination,’ language that rights advocates say raises legal and equal‑protection questions .</li><li>Prior policy pattern: Advocates point to recent administration actions — including the revocation of protected status for roughly 500,000 Haitians earlier in 2025 — as part of a broader shift in US migration policy priorities .</li><li>South African response: South African President Cyril Ramaphosa rejected the US government’s genocide claims and defended Pretoria’s land reform measures, saying the accusation is false .</li><li>Domestic critics: U.S. refugee organisations and some Democratic lawmakers said the cap and prioritisation reduce America’s moral standing and could be challenged as unlawful discrimination .</li></ul><blockquote>Justified by humanitarian concerns or is otherwise in the national interest. - President Donald Trump</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Trump administration: The administration said the reduced ceiling and selection priorities are justified on humanitarian grounds and serve the national interest, as stated in the Federal Register notice. (<a href='https://www.rt.com/news/627173-us-slashes-cap-refugees/'>RT.com</a>)</li><li>US refugee organisations: Groups working with refugees said capping admissions at this level and prioritising a single demographic lowers the country&#x27;s moral standing and undermines established resettlement systems. (<a href='https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2025/oct/31/first-thing-us-to-limit-refugee-numbers-to-7500-with-priority-for-white-south-africans'>The Guardian</a>)</li><li>South African government: President Cyril Ramaphosa dismissed the genocide allegation and defended land reform as an effort to address apartheid&#x27;s legacy. (<a href='https://www.rt.com/news/627173-us-slashes-cap-refugees/'>RT.com</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/explainers/trump-refugee-policy-white-south-africans-priority-controversy-13946627.html'>Why is Trump prioritising white South Africans as he slashes refugee admissions to historic low?</a> - firstpost.com</li><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cy40jj71243o'>Trump caps refugee admissions at record low - with most to be white South Africans</a> - bbc.com</li><li><a href='https://www.rt.com/news/627173-us-slashes-cap-refugees/'>Trump sets record-low cap on refugee admissions</a> - rt.com</li><li><a href='https://www.france24.com/en/americas/20251030-trump-refugee-admissions-white-south-africans'>Trump caps refugee admissions to record low, prioritising white South Africans</a> - france24.com</li><li><a href='https://www.lemonde.fr/en/international/article/2025/10/31/trump-s-administration-drastically-limits-refugee-admissions-to-mostly-white-south-africans_6746943_4.html'>Trump&#x27;s administration drastically limits refugee admissions to mostly white So